<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    *spoiler alert* I was actually bothered that they didn't explain what happened to him or who was involved in his death. It was almost like it left the<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    *spoiler alert* I was actually bothered that they didn't explain what happened to him or who was involved in his death. It was almost like it left the door open - maybe he wasn't really dead??? After 20+ years, I guess there is not going to be a sequel but it almost felt like it could've picked back up with the characters if he hadn't died. (Or maybe even if he really did.)<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
