<span id="freeTextContainer3333136716205179044">Really liked this thriller-- my favorite Baldacci yet. The two protagonists, Sidney Archer and Lee Sawyer prove to be very good partners despite the fact that they often seem to be on opposing sides. I especially enjoyed how resourceful Sidney was and the ways she finds to survive the search to find out what has happened to her missing husband. Is he dead or isn&apos;t he? <br/><br/>There are many characters in this books and many twists and turns, but it is written clearly enough that when you find out how al</span>
  <span id="freeText3333136716205179044" style="display:none">Really liked this thriller-- my favorite Baldacci yet. The two protagonists, Sidney Archer and Lee Sawyer prove to be very good partners despite the fact that they often seem to be on opposing sides. I especially enjoyed how resourceful Sidney was and the ways she finds to survive the search to find out what has happened to her missing husband. Is he dead or isn't he? <br /><br />There are many characters in this books and many twists and turns, but it is written clearly enough that when you find out how all the threads come together you can see how the plot thickened. j<br /><br />Great book to listen to on a summer road trip!</span>
  <a data-text-id="3333136716205179044" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

